claims:
1. A replaceable staple cartridge, comprising:
a cartridge body, comprising:
a first longitudinal slot;
a deck;
first sides extending downwardly from said deck, wherein an edge is defined between each said first side and said deck;
staple cavities defined in said deck; and
recesses defined in said deck proximal to said staple cavities;
staples removably stored in said staple cavities; and
a staple cartridge tray secured to said cartridge body, wherein said staple cartridge tray comprises:
a bottom comprising a second longitudinal slot defined therein; and
second sides extending upwardly from said bottom, wherein each said second side comprises a proximal end including a projection, wherein each said second side is adjacent to a said first side, and wherein each said projection wraps around a said edge and extends downwardly into a said recess defined in said deck.
2. The replaceable staple cartridge of claim 1, wherein each said projection comprises a hook portion.
3. The replaceable staple cartridge of claim 1, wherein said projections comprise first projections, wherein each said second side further comprises a distal portion including a second projection, wherein each said first side includes a distal portion including a side recess defined therein, and wherein each said second projection is positioned within a corresponding said side recess.
4. A replaceable staple cartridge, comprising:
a cartridge body, comprising:
a first longitudinal slot;
a tissue-contacting surface;
cartridge sides, wherein an edge is defined between each said cartridge side and said tissue-contacting surface;
staple cavities defined in said tissue-contacting surface; and
recesses defined in said tissue-contacting surface proximal to said staple cavities;
staples removably stored in said staple cavities; and
a staple cartridge pan attached to said cartridge body, wherein said staple cartridge pan comprises:
a base comprising a second longitudinal slot defined therein, wherein said first longitudinal slot and said second longitudinal slot are aligned with each other; and
pan sides extending upwardly from said base, wherein each said pan side comprises a proximal end including a projection extending laterally therefrom, wherein each said pan side extends over a said cartridge side, and wherein each said projection wraps around a said edge and extends downwardly into a said recess defined in said tissue-contacting surface.
5. The replaceable staple cartridge of claim 4, wherein each said projection comprises a hook portion.
6. The replaceable staple cartridge of claim 4, wherein said projections comprise first projections, wherein each said pan side further comprises a distal portion including a second projection, wherein each said cartridge side includes a distal portion including a side recess defined therein, and wherein each said second projection is positioned within a corresponding said side recess.
